

API
===

update dictionary
-----------------

This is passed up by the client when their location changes and returned by the
server.

{
    "twitter_user_name": "name",
    "twitter_profile_image_url": "http://someurl",
    "hashtag": "hashtag",
    "latitude": 123.456,
    "longitude": 123.456,
    "message": "this is the message",
    "update_datetime": "2009-10-28T06:47:11.690511"
}


/api/1/hashtag/THETAG
-------------------

GET - get a list of update dictionaries which match THETAG.

/api/1/update/
--------------

POST - a single update dictionary with (presumably) updated location info. The
twitter_user_name is used as the DataStore key_name. Any previous data for that
user is overwritten.

The value of update_datetime (if any) is ignored.

